span.p: This use case diagram represents interactions between customers, admins, delivery personnel, and warehouse logistics, encapsulating broad functionalities of the online shipment tracking system.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p: Customers can interact with the system to track their shipments, manage their accounts, and access notifications or support.

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: normal; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p: Admins are responsible for system management, ensuring updates, monitoring performance, and generating necessary reports.

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: normal; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p: Delivery personnel focus on maintaining delivery schedules, updating statuses, and resolving delivery-related issues.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p: Warehouse actions involve logistical operations like inventory management, sorting packages, and handling returns.

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: normal; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 316.646px; text-align: center;

span.p:
Use Case Summary:
- Customer: 15 use cases
- Admin: 10 use cases
- Delivery Guy: 6 use cases
- Warehouse: 6 use cases
- Total: 37 use cases.
